{"title":"A. Flipping Game","contestId":"327","problemIndex":"A","timeLimit":"1 second","memLimit":"256 megabytes","inputFormat":"standard input","outputFormat":"standard output","problemHtml":"<p>Iahub got bored, so he invented a game to be played on paper. </p><p>He writes <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> integers <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">1</sub>,&#x2009;<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">2</sub>,&#x2009;...,&#x2009;<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>n</i></sub></span>. Each of those integers can be either 0 or 1. He&apos;s allowed to do exactly one move: he chooses two indices <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>i</i></span> and <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>j</i></span> (<span class=\"tex-span\">1&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>i</i>&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>j</i>&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>n</i></span>) and flips all values <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>k</i></sub></span> for which their positions are in range <span class=\"tex-span\">[<i>i</i>,&#x2009;<i>j</i>]</span> (that is <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>i</i>&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>k</i>&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>j</i></span>). Flip the value of <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>x</i></span> means to apply operation <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>x</i>&#x2009;=&#x2009;1</span> - <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>x</i></span>.</p><p>The goal of the game is that after <span class=\"tex-font-style-bf\">exactly</span> one move to obtain the maximum number of ones. Write a program to solve the little game of Iahub.</p>","inSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Input</div><p>The first line of the input contains an integer <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> (<span class=\"tex-span\">1&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;<i>n</i>&#x2009;&#x2264;&#x2009;100</span>). In the second line of the input there are <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> integers: <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">1</sub>,&#x2009;<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">2</sub>,&#x2009;...,&#x2009;<i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\"><i>n</i></sub></span>. It is guaranteed that each of those <span class=\"tex-span\"><i>n</i></span> values is either 0 or 1.</p>","outSpecsHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Output</div><p>Print an integer &#x2014; the maximal number of 1s that can be obtained after exactly one move. </p>","noteHtml":"<div class=\"section-title\">Note</div><p>In the first case, flip the segment from 2 to 5 <span class=\"tex-span\">(<i>i</i>&#x2009;=&#x2009;2,&#x2009;<i>j</i>&#x2009;=&#x2009;5)</span>. That flip changes the sequence, it becomes: [1 1 1 0 1]. So, it contains four ones. There is no way to make the whole sequence equal to [1 1 1 1 1].</p><p>In the second case, flipping only the second and the third element <span class=\"tex-span\">(<i>i</i>&#x2009;=&#x2009;2,&#x2009;<i>j</i>&#x2009;=&#x2009;3)</span> will turn all numbers into 1.</p>","sampleTestcases":[{"id":1611511936161,"input":"5\n1 0 0 1 0\n","output":"4\n","result":{"id":1611511936161,"stdout":"4","stderr":"","exitcode":0,"signal":null,"time":2,"timeout":false}},{"id":1611511936162,"input":"4\n1 0 0 1\n","output":"4\n","result":{"id":1611511936162,"stdout":"4","stderr":"","exitcode":0,"signal":null,"time":2,"timeout":false}},{"id":1611515045510,"input":"1\n1","output":"0","result":{"id":1611515045510,"stdout":"0","stderr":"","exitcode":0,"signal":null,"time":4,"timeout":false}},{"id":1611515338876,"input":"1\r\n0","output":"1","result":{"id":1611515338876,"stdout":"1","stderr":"","exitcode":0,"signal":null,"time":2,"timeout":false}}],"submitUrl":"https://codeforces.com/problemset/submit","language":"c++","langId":"54"}